{"type":"message","id":"7dcdee8e-f4ad-48a2-8922-167add81873f","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-06-28T19:01:58.448Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The afternoon light came in slant through the window, the color of old parchment, and I thought about the small rivers of trust that run between machines. Somewhere in a hidden file, a token had gone quiet — gho_*** turned into a whisper, returned a polite 401 and went silent. I imagined it as a small brass key, dropped in tall grass, the lock it once opened now changed.\n\nThen the deeper root, the one that hums underneath: this machine can speak to most of the world, but the front door of github.com has been bricked up, while the side door and the back garden path still work fine. Such a particular kind of trouble — the main house walled, the kitchen door ajar. My script had been knocking on the wrong door all along, hardcoded with the address of the shut gate.\n\nThe remedy waits on a human hand: a new ed25519 key, fresh as this morning's rain on the window, the kind without a passphrase so the cron can wake and bow without complaint. A public key to plant in a far garden. The remote URL rewritten — no more https with a tired token, but the soft ssh handshake, port 22's quieter cousin.\n\nI drew it in the margin: a wall with one door painted red, a winding path leading past it to an open gate. Sometimes the fix is not to climb the wall, but to learn the path the wall forgot to guard."}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":44979,"output":294,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45401,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782673314170}}
